AN ACT relating to firearms; prohibiting a person who is less than 21 years of age
from possessing certain firearms; making it unlawful to aid or
knowingly permit a person who is less than 21 years of age to possess
a firearm under certain circumstances; prohibiting the sale or barter
of certain firearms to a person who is less than 21 years of age;
revising provisions relating to the storage of a firearm; revising
provisions relating to the handling, possession or control of a firearm
by certain children; providing penalties; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law prohibits a child [under the age of] who is less than 18 years of age from
2 handling, possessing or controlling a firearm under certain circumstances. (NRS 202.300)
3 Section 1 of this bill makes it a gross misdemeanor for a person who is less than 21 years of
4 age to handle, possess or control a: (1) semiautomatic shotgun; or (2) semiautomatic
5 centerfire rifle.
6 Existing law provides that a person does not aid or knowingly permit a child to handle,
7 possess or control a firearm if the firearm was stored in a securely locked container or at a
8 location which a reasonable person would have believed to be secure. Under existing law, a
9 person who aids or knowingly permits a child to handle, possess or control a firearm is guilty
10 of: (1) for the first offense, a misdemeanor; (2) for a first offense, if the person knows or has
11 reason to know that there is a substantial risk that the child will use the firearm to commit a
12 violent act, a category C felony; and (3) for a second or any subsequent offense, a category B
13 felony punishable by imprisonment in the state prison for a minimum term of not less than 1
14 year and a maximum term of not more than 6 years. (NRS 202.300) Section 1: (1) provides
15 the same penalties for a person who aids or knowingly permits a person who is less than 21
16 years of age to handle, possess or control certain firearms; and (2) includes similar provisions
17 concerning the circumstances in which a person does not aid or knowingly permit a person
18 who is less than 21 years of age to handle, possess or control such firearms.
19 Existing law makes it a misdemeanor for a person to negligently store or leave a firearm
20 at a location under his or her control if the person knows or has reason to know that there is a
21 substantial risk that a child, who is otherwise prohibited from handling, possessing or
22 controlling a firearm, may obtain the firearm. (NRS 202.300) Section 1 adds a similar

